From 75bc3b3acddabd7d626bf63fb3ba7e64ed43c8ad Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sumitkumar Pandit <hello@codedbysumit.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 12:53:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] feat(v4): colorful contact form + rainbow project tags +
 timeline + responsive fixes

Contact form (portfolio):
- Fixed email bug: was 'hello@sumitpandit.dev', now 'hello@codedbysumit.com' (matches domain)
- Each contact card icon+label gets its own accent color:
  Email=emerald, Phone=purple, Location=amber, GitHub=cyan, Twitter=pink, LinkedIn=blue
- Contact form now uses glass-card-glow (gradient border) with aurora glow
- Field labels colored (Name=emerald, Email=purple, Subject=amber, Message=cyan)
- Focus rings use brand colors matching each field's label
- Added 'Or email direct: hello@codedbysumit.com' fallback link inside the card

Portfolio Projects:
- Project tags (WEB3, BASE, AI, NLP, etc.) now rainbow-colored via badge-{accent}
  Each card's tags shift accent based on card index for visual variety
- 'Live demo' arrow button now colored gradient matching each project
- Project card corner glow now uses accent color instead of white

Portfolio Education & Journey Timeline:
- Timeline dots now colored gradient tiles per entry (was solid white)
- Timeline vertical line uses rainbow gradient (emerald -> purple -> amber)
- Section title uses gradient-text; graduation cap in emerald tile
- Entry titles colored by accent, year chips use badge-{accent}

Responsive fixes:
- Templates hero h1 now text-4xl on mobile, text-7xl on desktop (was overflowing)
- Same fix applied to blog, email-hub, free-tools, resources, tools hero titles
- Legal pages (privacy-policy, terms, affiliate-disclosure, about-author) heroes
  also now start at text-4xl for mobile safety
- Added break-words to all gradient-text hero titles to prevent overflow
